    "content_id": 800514,
    "reference_id": 203345,
    "title": "O trabalho do Espírito Santo",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "o trabalho do espírito santo",
    "language": "por",
    "content": "<p>Diferentes escritores do Novo Testamento destacaram vários aspectos do trabalho do Espírito Santo. O apóstolo João, por exemplo, destacou o papel do Espírito como mestre e revelador dos pensamentos e caminhos de Deus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:17\">João 14.17</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">15.26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13-John16:15\">16.13–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:20\">1 João 2.20</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">27</a>). O apóstolo Lucas focou na orientação e no poder do Espírito para espalhar a mensagem cristã (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">Atos 1.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:8-Acts4:12\">4.8–12</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:29-Acts8:40\">8.29–40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:9-Acts13:12\">13.9–12</a>). Enquanto isso, o apóstolo Paulo ofereceu uma perspectiva ampla do trabalho do Espírito.</p><p>Paulo ensina que Deus concede o Espírito Santo a todos que entram em um relacionamento de salvação com Jesus Cristo (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">1 Coríntios 6.19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:2-Gal3:5\">Gálatas 3.2–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">Efésios 1.13–14</a>). O Espírito traz nova vida em Cristo e confirma a salvação dos cristãos e sua identidade como filhos de Deus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1 Coríntios 6.11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2 Tessalonicenses 2.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">Romanos 8.9</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14-Rom8:17\">14–17</a>).</p><p>O Espírito Santo concede aos cristãos:</p><ul><li><p>poder sobre o pecado (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:4\">Romanos 8.1–4</a>);</p></li><li><p>poder para viver as virtudes cristãs (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">Gálatas 5.22–23</a>); e</p></li><li><p>poder para servir no ministério cristão (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1-1Cor12:31\">1 Coríntios 12.1–31</a>).</p></li></ul><p>Os cristãos devem &quot;ser cheios do Espírito Santo&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18\">Efésios 5.18</a>). Eles podem enfrentar uma luta entre seus desejos humanos e o Espírito. No entanto, podem agradar a Deus obedecendo à orientação e à força do Espírito (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:18\">Gálatas 5.16–18</a>).</p><p>O Espírito Santo ajuda os cristãos a entender os pensamentos e caminhos de Deus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:16\">1 Coríntios 2.9–16</a>). Ele fornece dons espirituais aos cristãos para apoiar a saúde geral da igreja (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1-1Cor12:31\">12.1–31</a>). O Espírito guia e fortalece a adoração à medida que os cristãos usam os dons dados por ele (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26-1Cor14:33\">14.26–33</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:39-1Cor14:40\">39–40</a>).</p><p>O Espírito Santo garante que os cristãos receberão todas as bênçãos que Deus prometeu (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:21-2Cor1:22\">2 Coríntios 1.21–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:1-2Cor5:5\">5.1–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">Efésios 1.13–14</a>). O Espírito apoia os cristãos e ora por eles quando estão fracos (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:27\">Romanos 8.26–27</a>). O objetivo do Espírito é fazer com que os cristãos se tornem &quot;parecidos com o Filho de Deus&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:28-Rom8:29\">Romanos 8.28–29</a>).</p><p><u>Passagens para estudo complementar</u></p><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:15-John14:17\">João 14.15–17</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">15.26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7-John16:15\">16.7–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">Atos 1.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">2.4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:32\">5.32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1-Acts6:7\">6.1–7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:29\">8.29</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:39\">39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">9.31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1-Acts13:5\">13.1–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:3\">14.3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:28\">15.28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:6\">16.6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">20.28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:4\">Romanos 8.1–4</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">9</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14-Rom8:17\">14–17</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:29\">26–29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:16\">1 Coríntios 2.9–16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">6.11</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1-1Cor12:31\">12.1–31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1-1Cor14:33\">14.1–33</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:39-1Cor14:40\">39–40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:22\">2 Coríntios 1.22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:5\">5.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:5\">Gálatas 3.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:18\">5.16–18</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">22–23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">Efésios 1.13–14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18\">5.18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2 Tessalonicenses 2.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16-2Tim3:17\">2 Timóteo 3.16–17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">Hebreus 2.4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:11\">3.7–11</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:15\">15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:8\">9.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:15-Heb10:17\">10.15–17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:11-1Pet1:12\">1 Pedro 1.11–12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:20-2Pet1:21\">2 Pedro 1.20–21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:20\">1 João 2.20</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">27</a></p>",
